e:T54d,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is a tankless water heater worth it in Nashville?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For households that stay 10+ years, currently run out of hot water at peak use, or want to recover the floor space — yes. For short-term homeowners or homes with adequate tank capacity already, the math is closer to break-even. We do an honest payback calculation during the in-home quote."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How often does a tankless water heater need to be serviced in Nashville?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Once a year for descaling, given Nashville's moderately hard water. Skipping descaling shortens unit life and eventually causes heat exchanger failure ($700–$1,200 replacement). Annual maintenance is the single best thing you can do for a tankless unit."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What size tankless water heater do I need for my Nashville home?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most Nashville single-family homes need a 180,000–199,000 BTU natural gas tankless unit (Rinnai RU199 / Navien NPE-240A2 class) to handle two showers and a kitchen sink simultaneously. Smaller homes with one bath can run on a 150,000 BTU class unit. We size it during the quote based on your actual fixture count and peak flow."}}]}6:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Services\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Tankless Water Heater Installation & Repair\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services/tankless-water-heaters\"}]}"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Service\",\"name\":\"Tankless Water Heater Installation & Repair\",\"description\":\"Tankless water heater installation, repair, and descaling in Nashville. Rinnai, Navien, Noritz, and Rheem. Endless hot water, 18–22 year service life, and real Nashville-specific advice on whether it's worth it.\",\"serviceType\":\"Tankless Water Heater Installation & Repair\",\"url\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services/tankless-water-heaters\",\"provider\":{\"@id\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com#business\"},\"areaServed\":[{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"East Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Downtown Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Green Hills\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Belle Meade & West Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Brentwood\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Franklin\"}]}"}}],["$","article",null,{"children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-ink/10","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-7","children":[["$","nav",null,{"aria-label":"Breadcrumb","className":"text-sm text-ink-muted mb-6","children":["$","ol",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-forest","children":"Home"}]}],["$","li",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/services","className":"hover:text-forest","children":"Services"}]}],["$","li",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"className":"text-ink","children":"Tankless Water Heaters"}]]}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-4","children":"Service"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-[1.05] text-ink mb-6","children":["Tankless Water Heater Installation & Repair"," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"italic text-forest","children":"in Nashville"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-display italic text-2xl text-ink-soft mb-7","children":"Endless hot water. Twenty years of it."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Tankless water heaters make sense for the right Nashville home — and don't for others. We install Rinnai, Navien, Noritz, and Rheem tankless units across the Nashville metro, and we'll tell you straight whether the conversion is worth the upfront cost for your specific house. We also do annual descaling and service on existing tankless units (Nashville's water is moderately hard and tankless units need yearly maintenance to hit their full service life)."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-5","children":["$","$Lf",null,{"defaultService":"tankless-water-heaters"}]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-editorial","children":[["$","div","Tankless vs. tank: who actually benefits",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Tankless vs. tank: who actually benefits"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Tankless makes financial sense if you (a) plan to stay in the house 10+ years, (b) currently run out of hot water during peak use, or (c) have a finished basement where you can recover the tank's floor space. The savings on a typical Nashville home are real but modest — about $80–$140/year on a natural-gas tankless versus a tank — so the payback math depends mostly on the installed cost difference and how long you'll live there. The 18–22 year service life means you'll typically skip one tank replacement cycle, which is where the real lifetime savings live."}]]}],["$","div","Installation: what changes from a tank install",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Installation: what changes from a tank install"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A tankless conversion in Nashville typically requires three upgrades beyond the unit itself: a larger gas line (most older homes have a half-inch line that won't feed the higher BTU demand — we run a three-quarter or one-inch line to the unit), stainless steel concentric venting (sealed combustion, exits through the side wall instead of up the flue), and a softener or scale inhibitor on the cold-water inlet for Nashville's moderately hard water. We factor all of this into the flat quote up front. Typical installed cost in the metro: $3,500–$6,500 depending on whether the gas line and venting need significant rework."}]]}],["$","div","Annual descaling — non-negotiable in Nashville",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Annual descaling — non-negotiable in Nashville"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Nashville water averages around 70–90 ppm hardness (moderately hard), and tankless heat exchangers scale up over time. We descale tankless units annually with a circulating vinegar or descaling-solution flush — takes about 45 minutes and resets the unit's efficiency. Skip this for three years in a row and you'll start seeing error codes, reduced flow rate, and eventually a $700–$1,200 heat exchanger replacement. Most homeowners book annual descaling in the fall before heating season. Our maintenance program covers it plus the tank flush on standard units."}]]}],["$","div","Pricing and what's included",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing and what's included"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Tankless install in the Nashville metro: $3,500–$6,500 fully installed (unit, gas line upgrade if needed, venting, install labor, permit, and Sullivan-registered manufacturer warranty). Annual descaling: $185. Tankless repair: $145 service call applied to the repair, then flat-rate quotes by repair type. We service all major brands even if we didn't install the unit. Warranty work on Rinnai, Navien, and Noritz units we install is handled in-house at no extra charge during the warranty period."}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-bone-100/60 border-y border-ink/10 py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-3","children":"Common questions"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-display text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-ink mb-10 leading-tight","children":["Frequently asked about ","tankless water heaters"," in Nashville."]}],["$","dl",null,{"className":"space-y-6","children":[["$","div","Is a tankless water heater worth it in Nashville?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"Is a tankless water heater worth it in Nashville?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"For households that stay 10+ years, currently run out of hot water at peak use, or want to recover the floor space — yes. For short-term homeowners or homes with adequate tank capacity already, the math is closer to break-even. We do an honest payback calculation during the in-home quote."}]]}],["$","div","How often does a tankless water heater need to be serviced in Nashville?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"How often does a tankless water heater need to be serviced in Nashville?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Once a year for descaling, given Nashville's moderately hard water. Skipping descaling shortens unit life and eventually causes heat exchanger failure ($700–$1,200 replacement). Annual maintenance is the single best thing you can do for a tankless unit."}]]}],["$","div","What size tankless water heater do I need for my Nashville home?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"What size tankless water heater do I need for my Nashville home?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Most Nashville single-family homes need a 180,000–199,000 BTU natural gas tankless unit (Rinnai RU199 / Navien NPE-240A2 class) to handle two showers and a kitchen sink simultaneously. Smaller homes with one bath can run on a 150,000 BTU class unit. We size it during the quote based on your actual fixture count and peak flow."}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-2xl mb-10","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-3","children":"Service areas"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-display text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-ink leading-tight","children":["We provide ","tankless water heaters"," across these Nashville-area neighborhoods:"]}]]}],["$","ul",null,{"className":"grid sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3","children":[["$","li","east-nashville",{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/areas/east-nashville","className":"block py-3 px-4 border border-ink/10 hover:border-forest hover:bg-bone-100/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-ink","children":"East Nashville"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"block text-xs text-ink-muted mt-0.5","children":"Nashville, TN"}]]}]}],["$","li","downtown-nashville",{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/areas/downtown-nashville","className":"block py-3 px-4 border border-ink/10 hover:border-forest hover:bg-bone-100/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-ink","children":"Downtown Nashville"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"block text-xs text-ink-muted mt-0.5","children":"Nashville, TN"}]]}]}],["$","li","green-hills",{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/areas/green-hills","className":"block py-3 px-4 border border-ink/10 hover:border-forest hover:bg-bone-100/50 transit